{
  "stem": "2067.2",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 12.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In the summer of 1940, I became a member of a group of young Dutch Jewish people at the sport club of [?",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Macaby ?].",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Some were friends of [?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Dottie's. ?] And she introduced me to them.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And a group of approximately eight young people-- young women and-- and young men-- had formed.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And we became close friends.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And in spite of the circumstances, and the Nazi occupation of Holland, we had a relatively [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] good and pleasant time in Holland in those days.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "In fact, for me it was one of the most happiest, the most happiest days of my life there.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Because I had a girlfriend.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And I knew that one day I-- I would get married to her.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And very good friends.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] In 19-- when 1941 came, there were already some restrictions.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Jews had to be-- there was a curfew on for Jews.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "We all had to be in at midnight.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Everything was black.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "There was a blackout in every occupied country of Europe.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And in '41 when the Nazi decrees started, life became more difficult for us.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "We were not allowed to go to public parks, to cinemas, to theaters.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "Anything where-- what-- where general public was admitted, Jews were excluded.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "So we were driven to be more together, to-- to visit each other.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "We were still allowed to have sports activity-- in this case tennis-- only in a Jewish club, to which I belonged.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "In February 1941 came the first open attack against Jews in Amsterdam for-- for some fictitious reason.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "Young men between the ages of 18 and 35 were suddenly round-- rounded up in Amsterdam on February 1941.",
      "word_count": 19
    }
  ],
